I was working on a couple of personal projects, and I've been using Claude Code for a while. Recently, I've been wanting to talk about my work publicly, but I started to think about how I would exactly talk about it, given the fact that I used AI to build some of the projects. There were entire features that I had Claude Code write for me, and although I did write a spec and design it, it still kinda feels a little wrong, like pseudo-plagiarism.&lt;p&gt;Wanted to know how everyone is talking about their work while using AI. Do y'all mention the fact that you're using AI, or do you keep mum about it?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Comments URL: &lt;a href="https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48203050"&gt;https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48203050&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
